allow pathogens to move into the surrounding air.""Toilets have a u-shaped drain to trap fluids and odor. However, the Washington Post reported in 2003 that faulty plumbing can cause backwash from toilets, which led to a SARS outbreak at another residential tower in Hong Kong.""Citing an infectious disease expert, Live Science explains that the new virus, now named COVID-19, could in fact transmit via feces, although aerosols from coughing and sneezing are still believed to be the main infection mechanism."SOURCES: South Morning China Post, Live Science, World Health Organization, The Washington Posthttps://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/health-environment/article/3049921/tsing-yi-residents-evacuated-hong-kong-healthhttps://www.livescience.com/coronavirus-spread-building-pipes.htmlhttps://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/releases/2003/pr70/en/https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/politics/2003/04/18/in-hong-kong-apartment-tower-sars-virus-spread-through-plumbing/99bcd25f-de85-472a-b084-4f847e0dac9a/***]]></description>
